						               													<description>In &amp;#231;&amp;#132;&amp;#161;&amp;#233;&amp;#153;&amp;#144;&amp;#229;&amp;#155;&amp;#158;&amp;#230;&amp;#174;&amp;#181; (Mugenkai Dan), players are climbing an &amp;quot;infinite&amp;quot; staircase; to create the staircase, the game has 2 boards showing six stairs each. One of the available actions in the game moves one of the boards to the other end, such that the stairs will go on.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To setup, each player takes a die of their color and a matching set of action tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each round, the players will perform two actions each.  First, they take turns choosing action tiles from their hand and placing them face down in a queue.  After the first tile is placed, future tiles are placed to the left or right, but once the 6 tiles have been placed, they will execute from left to right.  The actions do such things as move your dice up the stairs; move an entire stair board; score points; and swap dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to score 5 points will win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
